.TH "SHELLY" "1" "Dec 2025" "Shelly CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
shelly-debug-coiot - Show CoIoT/CoAP status


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshelly debug coiot  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show CoIoT (CoAP over Internet of Things) status for a device.

.PP
CoIoT is used by Gen1 and some Gen2 devices for local discovery and
real-time status updates via multicast UDP.

.PP
This command shows:
- CoIoT enabled/disabled status
- Multicast settings
- Peer configuration (for unicast mode)
- Update period settings


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for coiot

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output as JSON


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	Config file (default $HOME/.config/shelly/config.yaml)

.PP
\fB--log-categories\fP=""
	Filter logs by category (comma-separated: network,api,device,config,auth,plugin)

.PP
\fB--log-json\fP[=false]
	Output logs in JSON format

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format (table, json, yaml, template)

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--template\fP=""
	Go template string for output (use with -o template)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=0]
	Increase verbosity (-v=info, -vv=debug, -vvv=trace)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Show CoIoT status
  shelly debug coiot living-room

  # Output as JSON
  shelly debug coiot living-room --json
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBshelly-debug(1)\fP
